The tribal chief. The head of the table. The top guy in the industry. No further explanation needed.
>Sheamus
Gets more over than he's ever been in his career. Puts on BANGER after BANGER after BANGER. Prospects will only continue to skyrocket given he's being booked by Triple H who has always been in his corner.
>Triple H
Finally realized his decades long ambition of climbing to the top of WWE and running the show. Whether or not you think he's doing a good job of it, which personally I don't, I think he sucks, this is objectively a big win regardless and a huge unKWAB from when his version of NXT was torn apart and he almost died.
>Stephanie McMahon
Jannettied her brother and ousts her father from his own company to take it for herself and her husband. Big win.
>Austin Theory
The next The Guy under Vince. Seemed like that was all going to fall apart for him and he'd be a KWABOTY candidate. Nope. His push is back on track. Massive unKWAB. This guy is essentially set for life as the next guy WWE forces audiences to consider a star. And in the end, WWE always gets its way with this. Big win.
>JONAH/Bronson Reed
From KWABOTY contender to beating Okada to telling NJPW to fuck off and getting that bag from WWE. Money and miles. Big winner right here.
>Dominik Mysterio
Heel turn took him from easily the worst performer on weekly TV to being a pretty over heel duo with Rhea. He might be one of the most blatant cases of a shitter getting ahead due to nepotism ever seen in wrestling history but this has turned into a good year for him.

you're seeing him peak again. After he won the Dream Gate he had an alright run at the top but was unseated by Naruki Doi.

Ben was essentially one of the leaders of the DG unit but really got outshined on the mic by YAMATO and Kzy so he just sort of fated into the background.
After the Generational War he joined YAMATO's High-End unit and again wasn't really the focal point. That changed when Ben defected and joined Gold Class where he changed his character from a silent-ish badass to a cocky badass instead.

As a huge fan of professional wrestling, you had always dreamed of one day stepping into the ring with your hero, Kenny Omega. So when you heard that Kenny was coming to town for a series of matches, you knew that you had to be there.

You arrived at the arena early on the day of the match, determined to get a good spot. You waited in line for hours, chatting with other fans and excitedly anticipating the main event.

Finally, the doors opened and you made your way to your seat. The arena was packed, and the energy was electric. You could hardly contain your excitement as the wrestlers took to the ring, one by one.

And then, finally, it was time for the main event. Kenny Omega stepped into the ring, and the crowd went wild. You were on the edge of your seat, cheering and chanting along with everyone else.

As the match got underway, you couldn't believe your luck. Kenny was right in front of you, performing all of his signature moves and putting on a show for the ages.

But then, something unexpected happened. The referee went down, and the match was thrown into chaos. Suddenly, Kenny turned to you and gestured for you to come into the ring.

Without hesitation, you climbed up onto the apron and stepped into the ring. You couldn't believe it – you were about to face off against your hero, Kenny Omega.

The crowd went wild as the two of you locked up. You gave it your all, and Kenny matched you move for move. It was a dream come true.

In the end, the match was a draw. You and Kenny hugged and celebrated together, and the crowd gave you both a standing ovation.

As you left the arena that night, you knew that you would never forget this amazing experience. You had gotten to wrestle your hero, Kenny Omega, and nothing could ever top that.
